The paper examines the effects of online sharing mechanisms on peer adoption, which falls under the category of social influence and social networks. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves a large-scale field experiment on Facebook, which suggests that it could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the design of online systems, which could relate to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The joint discrete choice model used in the study could also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves modeling user behavior. Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.HC, and cs.IR.
